articles.title: Greece raises the Bar: Golden Visa investment threshold hits €800,000
articles.description: Greece's Golden Visa program, which started in 2013 and initially required a €250,000 investment for residency, is set to increase its threshold to €800,000 starting in September 2024. articles.title: Defence Stocks: Structural changes are stronger than negative narrative, 15 stocks from defense ecosystem, with possible return of up to 21 to 39%
articles.description: May 2024, everyone is rushing to buy defence stocks. On the day of election results, they were badly battered. Come July a number of them are higher than what they were on the day of the election results. Come August, they are not performing as well as they were in the first five months of 2024, The result, a narrative on the street starts that they are overpriced and to add icing on the cake, some fund managers make statements about not owning them or that they have booked profit in them. The question to be asked from these so-called alpha fund managers, some of them who run PMS, is whether they bought these defence stocks 5 years back when no one was looking at them or they bought just as they became momentum stocks. Sometimes narratives get formed on the street, which may lead to wrong decisions if one does not question them.
